Hill:
Intermittent social runners
Benefit from targeted internal data and external data
In order to assess and enhance race performance in an engaging manner.

SubHill:
An intermittent social runner signs up for a RAM-organized race through the consolidated web platform (a website + mobile app, to which runners can log on any time, from anywhere).

Story:
As an intermittent social runner
I want to be able to view on all RAM race information from one RAM platform available both in website and app formats
So that I can sign up from a single RAM login account

Acceptance Criteria:
Given I'm an internittent social runner who wants to register for a RAM race
When I sign in my RAM account on RAM website/ RAM application
Then I can sign up any RAM race by this account

Version 2
Acceptance Criteria:
Given I'm an internittent social  
When I sign in my RAM account on RAM website/ RAM application to register for a RAM race
Then I can sign up (and register?) for any RAM race through this account
